This paper is primarily focused on deep learning-based underwater image enhancement, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of various deep learning architectures and loss functions, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also touches upon the use of robotics for underwater imaging, which is relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
